A.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Brutal%20Hamas%20Attack%20Shifts%20Israel%20From%20Managing%20To%20Destroying%20It%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFor%2016%20years%2C%20Israeli%20governments%20worked%20to%20manage%20the%20Hamas%20leaders%20in%20Gaza%2C%20not%20topple%20them.%20The%20Islamist%20group%20rejected%20Israel's%20existence%20and%20engaged%20in%20violence%2C%20but%20kept%20order%20over%20the%20territory.%20Better%20Hamas%20than%20chaos.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20carnage%20last%20weekend%2C%20when%20Hamas%20militants%20killed%20hundreds%20of%20Israeli%20civilians%20after%20a%20sophisticated%20breach%20of%20the%20border%20fence%2C%20has%20shifted%20official%20views.%20Now%2C%20the%20aim%20is%20to%20destroy%20the%20organization's%20military%20capability%20and%20kill%20its%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELeft%20unsaid%20in%20Israel%20but%20widely%20assumed%20is%20that%2C%20when%20the%20war%20ends%2C%20Hamas%20will%20no%20longer%20rule%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20announcing%20the%20formation%20of%20an%20emergency%20unity%20government%20on%20Wednesday%20night%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20referred%20to%20the%20Islamic%20State%20organization%20from%20the%20previous%20decade%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BHamas%20is%20ISIS%2C%20and%20we%20will%20crush%20and%20eliminate%20it%20just%20as%20the%20world%20crushed%20and%20eliminated%20ISIS.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELieutenant%20Colonel%20Richard%20Hecht%2C%20a%20military%20spokesman%2C%20told%20reporters%20on%20Thursday%3A%20%26quot%3BRight%20now%2C%20we%20are%20focused%20on%20taking%20out%20their%20senior%20leadership%2C%20not%20only%20the%20military%20but%20also%20their%20government%20leadership.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Mowing%20Lawn'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20change%20from%20the%20previous%20military%20policy%20of%20occasional%20invasions%2C%20harsh%20but%20limited%2C%20sometimes%20referred%20to%20as%20%26quot%3Bmowing%20the%20lawn%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20a%20task%20to%20which%20one%20is%20required%20to%20return%20repeatedly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAny%20operation%20against%20the%20militant%20group%20is%20destined%20to%20result%20in%20more%20civilian%20deaths%20and%20raise%20diplomatic%20dilemmas.%20Turkey%20has%20already%20signaled%20a%20shift%20away%20from%20the%20intense%20diplomacy%20that%20was%20underway%20to%20normalize%20ties%20with%20Israel%20after%20years%20of%20estrangement.%20Rulers%20from%20Saudi%20Arabia%20to%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20could%20follow%20if%20public%20opinion%20in%20their%20countriesturns%20increasingly%20hostile%20to%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20former%20top%20military%20officer%20who%20remains%20in%20close%20touch%20with%20the%20army%2C%20speaking%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity%2C%20said%20when%20the%20war%20ends%2C%20Israel%20may%20set%20up%20a%20temporary%20military%20regime%20and%20hand%20Gaza%20over%20to%20some%20international%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20head%20of%20the%20opposition%2C%20Yair%20Lapid%2C%20who%20didn't%20join%20the%20new%20government%20with%20Benny%20Gantz%2C%20another%20opposition%20leader%2C%20said%20this%20week%20on%20French%20television%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20endgame%20is%20there%20will%20be%20no%20Hamas%20in%20Gaza.%26quot%3B%20His%20goal%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20for%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%2C%20which%20holds%20power%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20recognizes%20Israel%2C%20would%20take%20over.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERequests%20for%20comment%20from%20the%20prime%20minister's%20office%20and%20the%20defense%20minister%20weren't%20immediately%20answered.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELittle%20Mercy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsraeli%20officials%20are%20showing%20no%20mercy%20for%20ordinary%20Gazans%20in%20their%20campaign%2C%20having%20cut%20electricity%2C%20fuel%20and%20food%20shipments%20from%20Israel%20and%20given%20residents%20few%20choices%20of%20where%20to%20hide%20as%20heavy%20bombings%20continue.%20At%20least%201%2C350%20have%20been%20killed%20to%20date.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Elai%20Rettig%2C%20an%20expert%20of%20the%20geopolitics%20of%20energy%20and%20environment%20at%20Israel's%20Bar-Ilan%20University%2C%20a%20power%20cut%20will%20result%20in%20water%20shortages%20in%20a%20week%20or%20two.%20That's%20likely%20to%20hinder%20access%20to%20health%20care%20or%20drinkable%20water%20for%20Gaza's%202%20million%20people%2C%20half%20of%20whom%20are%20under%20the%20age%20of%2018.%20Israeli%20authorities%20are%20worried%20about%20a%20humanitarian%20corridor%20into%20Egypt%2C%20saying%20that%20would%20allow%20Hamas%20leaders%20to%20sneak%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERettig%20also%20said%20Hamas%20has%20been%20given%20aid%20to%20fix%20and%20upgrade%20the%20electrical%20system%20in%20Gaza%20but%20hadn't%20done%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHostage%20Fate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3ENearly%20all%20analysts%20in%20Israel%20believe%20ground%20troops%20are%20headed%20in%20after%20the%20aerial%20pounding.%20Many%20of%20the%20dozens%20of%20Israeli%20hostages%20and%20some%20of%20the%20soldiers%20seem%20likely%20to%20meet%20their%20deaths.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20that%20too%20is%20quietly%20discussed%20as%20a%20price%20the%20country%20is%20willing%20to%20pay%20to%20end%20Hamas's%20hold%20on%20Gaza%20and%20send%20a%20broader%20message%20to%20the%20country's%20enemies%2C%20including%20Hezbollah%20in%20Lebanon%20and%20its%20Iranian%20sponsor.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael's%20biggest%20deployment%20of%20reserves%20in%20its%20history%20shows%20its%20leaders%20are%20aware%20how%20difficult%20it%20might%20be%20to%20crush%20Hamas%2C%20but%20eliminating%20it%20from%20Gaza%20is%20an%20even%20bigger%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20Israeli%20cross-border%20operation%20into%20southern%20Lebanon%20to%20attack%20Iran-backed%20Hezbollah%20in%202006%20ended%20in%20massive%20casualties%20following%20more%20than%20a%20month%20of%20fighting.%20Since%20Saturday's%20attack%2C%20Hezbollah%20has%20fired%20into%20Israel%20every%20now%20and%20then%2C%20a%20reminder%20that%20it%20may%20be%20tempted%20to%20open%20a%20new%20front%20in%20the%20war%20after%20the%20Gaza%20ground%20offensive%20begins.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20direness%20of%20the%20rhetoric%20is%20driven%20by%20the%20images%20of%20inhumanity%20on%20display%20last%20Saturday%20and%20the%20collective%20memory%20of%20Jews%20being%20slaughtered%20in%20the%20Holocaust%20and%20in%20pogroms%20a%20century%20ago.%20It%20has%20made%20many%20Israelis%20feel%20this%20is%20a%20war%20for%20their%20very%20existence%2C%20and%20they%20must%20show%20how%20tough%20they%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERetired%20Major%20General%20Yaakov%20Amidror%2C%20who%20was%20Netanyahu's%20national%20security%20adviser%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20cannot%20go%20back%20to%20square%20one.%20This%20will%20take%20a%20few%20months.%20How%20many%20will%20be%20killed%3F%20Many%2C%20many.%20It's%20up%20to%20Hamas%2C%20which%20operates%20from%20populated%20areas.%20This%20is%20the%20last%20time%20we%20allow%20Hamas%20to%20be%20strong%20enough%20to%20attack%20Israel.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAsked%20who%20will%20rule%20Gaza%20when%20Israel%20is%20finished%2C%20he%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20people%20in%20Gaza%20will%20have%20to%20decide%20what%20is%20next.%20That%20is%20their%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697177640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2F255eis3_israel-gaza-reuters_625x300_11_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhow-brutal-hamas-attack-shifts-israel-from-managing-to-destroying-it-4477074%22%2C%22summar