20Delhi%3C%2Fi%3E%20makes%20its%20lumbering%20way%20through%20a%20string%20of%20gunfights%20and%20slugfests%2C%20hints%20of%20perfunctory%20romance%20(and%20loads%20of%20bromance%2C%20too)%2C%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20toxic%20masculinity%20(of%20desperate%20men%20who%20believe%20that%20the%20world%20is%20theirs%20for%20the%20asking)%20and%20an%20overload%20of%20riddles%20(which%20are%20posed%20by%20a%20robber-baron%20to%20begin%20with%20and%20then%20assume%20the%20nature%20of%20a%20mind%20game%20between%20him%20and%20his%20accomplices%20and%20adversaries).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20series%20revolves%20around%20Arjun%20Bhatia%20(Tahir%20Raj%20Bhasin)%2C%20who%2C%2017%20years%20after%20the%20Partition%20riots%2C%20has%20learnt%20to%20live%20down%20his%20past%20and%20go%20for%20broke%20in%20a%20dog-eat-dog%20world.%20He%20is%20a%20master-mechanic%20driven%20by%20a%20passion%20for%20cars%20that%20enable%20him%20to%20zoom%20into%20the%20big%20league%20in%20a%20hurry.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fq1rBgcuLLWQ%3Fsi%3D2KCbLEGfBqOjoj50%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20his%20loyal%20friend%20Nilendu%20alias%20Bangali%20(Anjum%20Sharma)%2C%20the%20young%20hustler%20works%20for%20Jagan%20Seth%20(Vinay%20Pathak)%2C%20a%20businessman%20with%20political%20ambitions.%20Arjun%20falls%20in%20love%20with%20a%20wealthy%20man's%20daughter%20Sanjana%20(Mehreen%20Pirzada)%20but%20his%20path%2C%20as%20he%20is%20to%20find%20out%20soon%2C%20isn't%20strewn%20with%20roses.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3ESultan%20of%20Delhi%3C%2Fi%3E%20begins%20with%20a%20meeting%20of%20a%20half%20a%20dozen%20ageing%20men%20whose%20writ%20runs%20over%20the%20city's%20underworld.%20The%20convener%20of%20the%20gathering%20of%20rogues%20is%20Farooq%20Mastaan%20(Anil%20George)%2C%20who%20advises%20the%20gang%20lords%20to%20work%20in%20unison%20and%20names%20Arjun%20as%20a%20first%20among%20equals%2C%20the%20man%20who%20will%20henceforth%20call%20the%20shots.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20couple%20of%20the%20old%20fogeys%20do%20not%20take%20kindly%20to%20the%20prospect%20of%20a%20rookie%20being%20handed%20the%20reins%20of%20their%20operations.%20Arjun%20whips%20out%20a%20gun.%20Cut.%20The%20rest%20is%20more%20hysteria%20than%20history%2C%20peppered%20with%20exploits%20of%20men%20going%20all%20out%20to%20change%20their%20individual%20and%20collective%20destinies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EArjun%20has%20his%20own%20way%20of%20dealing%20with%20tricky%20situations%20such%20as%20the%20one%20in%20the%20opening%20sequence.%20There%20is%20worse%20ahead.%20His%20principal%20foe%20is%20Rajinder%20Pratap%20Singh%20(Nishant%20Dahiya)%2C%20son%20of%20a%20businessman%20who%20made%20his%20fortune%20by%20profiting%20from%20the%20misery%20of%20refugees.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20lines%20separating%20good%20and%20evil%20are%20not%20only%20blurred%20but%20completely%20eliminated%20as%20Rajinder%2C%20egged%20on%20by%20Shankari%20(Anupriya%20Goenka)%2C%20the%20manipulative%20mistress%20he%20has%20willingly%20inherited%20from%20his%20father%2C%20conspires%20to%20push%20Arjun%20off%20the%20pedestal%20that%20Jagan%20Seth%20has%20given%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20lacklustre%20show%20does%20away%20with%20the%20layers%20that%20are%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20the%20book%20it%20is%20adapted%20from%20-%20Sultan%20of%20Delhi%3A%20Ascension%2C%20written%20by%20Arnab%20Ray.%20The%20narrative%20vacuum%20that%20is%20created%20as%20a%20result%20is%20hard%20to%20offset.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20titular%20city%2C%20the%20tumultuous%201960s%20and%20the%20tough%20men%20who%20joust%20for%20control%20over%20a%20crime%20network%20run%20by%20slimy%20businessmen%20and%20smarmy%20politicians%20are%20mere%20cardboard%20pieces%20in%20a%20haphazard%20jigsaw%20that%20does%20not%20quite%20add%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20crucial%20elements%20of%20the%20plot%2C%20especially%20the%20setting%2C%20are%20short%20on%20authenticity.%20Neither%20the%20milieu%20nor%20the%20period%20creates%20an%20impression.%20Nobody%20in%20the%20show%20lives%20in%20real%20homes.%20Everybody%20owns%20a%20mansion%20that%20sprawls%20across%20of%20acres%20of%20land%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20nowhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20does%20not%20see%20enough%20of%20Delhi%2C%20barring%20establishing%20aerial%20shots%20of%20Qutub%20Minar%20at%20different%20times%20of%20day%20and%20night.%20These%20feel%20more%20like%20stock%20footage%20than%20fundamental%20parts%20of%20the%20visual%20design.%20The%20streets%2C%20the%20houses%2C%20even%20a%20ritzy%20hotel%20and%20its%20environs%20-%20nothing%20bears%20any%20resemblance%20to%20what%20the%20city%20might%20have%20looked%20like%20back%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEarly%20on%2C%20%3Ci%3ESultan%20of%20Delhi%3C%2Fi%3E%20offers%20glimpses%20of%20a%20Lajpat%20Nagar%20refugee%20camp%2C%20where%20a%20boy%20ends%20up%20with%20his%20father%20after%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20family%20has%20been%20wiped%20out%20in%20Lahore.%20It%20also%20takes%20the%20audience%20into%20Chawri%20Bazaar%2C%20Paharganj%20and%20other%20parts%20of%20Old%20Delhi.%20They%20are%20akin%20to%20drop-in%20settings%2C%20as%20counterfeit%20as%20the%20show's%20general%20depiction%20of%20people%2C%20places%20and%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EParts%20of%20%3Ci%3ESultan%20of%20Delhi%3C%2Fi%3E%20play%20out%20in%20Calcutta.%20Here%20too%2C%20one%20sees%20nothing%20of%20the%20city.%20The%20show's%20understanding%20of%20leftist%20political%20activism%20of%20the%201960s%20is%20limited%20to%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20filmmaker%20simply%20called%20Roy%20Babu.%20He%20masterminds%20bank%20heists.%20It%20isn't%20robbery%2C%20it%20is%20rebellion%2C%20the%20man%20insists.%20The%20money%20belongs%20to%20the%20poor%2C%20he%20asserts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Delhi%2C%20too%2C%20all%20that%20it%20takes%20for%20a%20moneyed%20man%20to%20get%20an%2