t%3D%5C%223461%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E10%20October%202023%2C%20Israel%2C%20Kfar%20Aza%3A%20Israeli%20forces%20extracting%20dead%20bodies%20of%20Israeli%20residents%20from%20a%20destroyed%20house%20as%20fighting%20between%20Israeli%20troops%20and%20Islamist%20Hamas%20militants%20continues.%3Cp%3EIlia%20Yefimovich%2Fpicture%20alliance%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3ESocial%20media%20has%20been%20rife%20with%20disturbing%20images%20and%20hot%20takes%20since%20the%20Hamas%20terror%20attacks%20in%20Israel.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EBut%20experts%20say%20social%20media%20is%20ill-suited%20for%20conversations%20about%20the%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20prioritization%20of%20user%20engagement%20means%20extreme%20takes%20and%20misinformation%20can%20easily%20spread.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20past%20six%20days%20on%20social%20media%20have%20been%20a%20heartbreaking%20and%20deeply%20disturbing%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVideos%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideo-kidnapped-woman-begs-hamas-fighters-not-to-kill-her-2023-10%5C%22%3Eyoung%20Israelis%20taken%20hostage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20begging%20for%20their%20lives.%20Accounts%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkibbutz-attack-survivor-says-hamas-turned-home-into-pure-hell-2023-10%5C%22%3Ekibbutzim%3C%2Fa%3E%20littered%20with%20the%20bodies%20of%20babies%20and%20the%20elderly%20killed%20by%20Hamas%20militants.%20Photos%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgaza-israel-airstrikes-children-doctors-without-borders-2023-10%5C%22%3EGazan%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%20covered%20in%20blood%20and%20the%20bodies%20of%20Palestinians%20killed%20in%20Israel's%20counterattacks%20carried%20through%20the%20demolished%20neighborhoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20to%20add%20to%20the%20devastation%2C%20blatant%20misinformation%2C%20and%20countless%20hot%20takes%20are%20shared%20and%20reshared%2C%20often%20by%20people%20who%20may%20not%20actually%20know%20much%20about%20the%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20takes%20are%20the%20norm%20on%20social%20media.%20But%20this%20moment%20especially%20highlights%20the%20limitations%20of%20trying%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20a%2075-year-old%20conflict%20by%20reading%20an%20infographic%20that%20was%20designed%20to%20evoke%20an%20emotional%20response%20and%20provide%20an%20illusion%20of%20moral%20clarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20shortcut%20and%20the%20dumbing%20down%20of%20a%20situation%20that's%20been%20complicated%20since%201947%2C%26quot%3B%20Alison%20Dagnes%2C%20a%20political%20scientist%20and%20professor%20in%20political%20media%2C%20told%20Insider%20of%20the%20short%20online%20takes%20that%20often%20get%20widely%20shared.%20%26quot%3BA%20situation%20that%20nobody%20has%20ever%20been%20able%20to%20solve.%20It's%20not%20suited%20for%20a%20medium%20where%20there's%20only%20room%20for%20the%20most%20brief%2C%20emotional%2C%20visceral%20reaction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDagnes%20said%20the%20nature%20of%20social%20media%20and%20the%20attention%20economy%20means%20that%20there%20is%20a%20financial%20incentive%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20platforms%20to%20keep%20users%20scrolling%2C%20clicking%2C%20commenting.%20And%20it's%20often%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fhow-tech-platforms-fuel-u-s-political-polarization-and-what-government-can-do-about-it%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtroversial%2C%20hot%20takes%20that%20get%20higher%20engagement%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20therefore%20get%20shared%20or%20served%20up%20to%20more%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20much%20easier%2C%20and%20emotionally%20appealing%2C%20to%20clearly%20define%20the%20good%20guys%20and%20the%20bad%20guys%20and%20leave%20it%20at%20that%2C%20she%20said.%20But%20that's%20exactly%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTrying%20to%20explain%20the%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%20in%20one%20picture%20is%20almost%20like%20a%20Second%20City%20sketch.%20It's%20like%20'Name%20That%20Tune%2C'%20but%20with%20one%20note.%20You%20can't%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20impossible%20task%2C%20to%20take%20something%20so%20nuanced%20and%20so%20complicated%20and%20turn%20it%20into%20something%20that's%20simple%20enough%20to%20digest%20quickly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20stuff%20that's%20good%20and%20real%20and%20thoughtful%20is%20boring%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPolarization%20and%20misinformation%20are%20common%20on%20social%20media%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKen%20Paulson%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Free%20Speech%20Center%20at%20Middle%20Tennessee%20State%20University%2C%20agreed%20that%20social%20media%20does%20not%20lend%20itself%20to%20useful%20conversations%20on%20the%20broader%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Saturday's%20Hamas%20terror%20attack%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fochaopt.org%2Fcontent%2Fhostilities-gaza-strip-and-israel-flash-update-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekilled%20at%20least%201%2C300%2C%20and%20Israel's%20brutal%20response%20in%20Gaza%20that%20has%20killed%20at%20least%201%2C400%20are%20no%20exception%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20social%20media%20world%2C%20the%20impulse%20is%20to%20reach%20a%20conclusion%20based%20on%20your%20emotions%20and%20share%20it%20with%20the%20world%20as%20quickly%20and%20ferociously%20as%20you%20can%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20social%20media%2C%20conversations%20like%20this%20would%20typically%20happen%20over%20coffee%20or%20at%20the%20workplace%20%E2%80%94%20likely%20still%20with%20some%20disagreement.%20But%20due%20to%20social%20media's%20ability%20to%20supercharge%20every%20take%20and%20exchange%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20who%20comments%20on%20this%20is%20convinced%20they're%20right%20and%20anyone%20who%20expresses%20another%20opinion%20is%20morally%20corrupt.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Palestinian%20men%20carry%20away%20the%20body%20of%20a%20person%20killed%20by%20Israeli%20bombardment%20along%20a%20debris-littered%20street%20in%20al-Karama%20district%20in%20Gaza%20City%20on%20October%2011%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652881876561dd877e799345%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPalestinian%20men%20carry%20away%20the%20body%20of%20a%20person%20killed%20by%20Israeli%20bombardment%20along%20a%20debris-littered%20street%20in%20al-Karama%20district%20in%20Gaza%20City%20on%20October%2011%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EMohammed%20Abed%2FAFP%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESocial%20media%20can%20of%20course%20be%20used%20to%20spread%20important%20information%20or%20raise%20awareness%20about%20issues%20that%20have%20been%20ignored%20by%20the%20broader%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20many%20social%20media%20users%20fall%20victim%20to%20misinformation%2C%20which%20has%20spread%20like%20wildfire%20even%20in%20the%20first%20week%20of%20this%20war.%20Users%20also%20often%20fail%20to%20question%20how%20informed%20the%20writer%20of%20any%20particular%20post%20actually%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDagnes%20said%20that%20just%20by%20virtue%20of%20posting%20something%2C%20anyone%20can%20be%20an%20expert%20to%20social%20media%20users%20%E2%80%94%20never%20mind%20that%20person's%20actual%20qualifications%20or%20life%20experience.%20So%20even%20if%20people%20are%20engaging%20more%20with%20the%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%2C%20they're%20often%20engaging%20with%20posts%20that%20are%20false%2C%20misleading%2C%20or%20simply%20omit%20relevant%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSocial%20media's%20greatest%20strength%20is%20thus%20its%20original%20sin%3A%20These%20sites%20are%20excellent%20at%20making%20you%20%3Cem%3Efeel%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0connected%20and%20informed%2C%20frequently%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20actually%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ebeing%3C%2Fem%3E%20informed%2C%26quot%3B%20Charlie%20Warzel%20wrote%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Ftechnology%2Farchive%2F2023%2F10%2Fsocial-media-infrastructure-news-algorithms%2F675614%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Atlantic%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Thursday.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20to%20say%20nothing%20of%20the%20psychological%20toll%20that%20comes%20from%20staring%20at%20the%20raw%20feed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPosting%20is%20easier%20than%20actually%20learning%20about%20the%20conflict%20or%20listening%20to%20victims%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20is%20that%20if%20you%2C%20as%20an%20individual%2C%20have%20not%20paid%20attention%20to%20the%20conflict%20before%20now%2C%20you%20do%20not%20have%20to%20post%20or%20share%20a%20big%20take%20on%20what%20led%20to%20this%20moment%20or%20what%20should%20happen%20going%20forward.%20In%20an%20op-ed%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.msnbc.com%2Fopinion%2Fmsnbc-opinion%2Fisrael-hamas-conflict-social-media-pressure-rcna119596%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMSNBC%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Rachel%20E.%20Greenspan%2C%20who%20is%20Jewish%2C%20wrote%20that%20she%20did%20not%20expect%20anyone%2C%20her%20Jewish%20and%20non-Jewish%20friends%20alike%2C%20to%20post%20anything%20about%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20reality%2C%20there%20are%20no%20points%20to%20be%20accrued%20by%20Instagram%20Stories.%20There%20are%20no%20winnings%20for%20those%20who%20post%20the%20most%20widely%20approved%20infographics%2C%20no%20penalties%20for%20those%20who%20choose%20not%20to%20post%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BGiven%20all%20the%20horrible%20events%20that%20are%20happening%20in%20the%20world%20at%20any%20given%20moment%2C%20if%20there%20were%20such%20penalties%2C%20then%20