3Cp%3EBut%20the%20lessons%20of%20Ukraine%20aren't%20that%20straightforward.%20Experts%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwarontherocks.com%2F2022%2F09%2Fthe-tank-is-not-obsolete-and-other-observations-about-the-future-of-combat%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20argued%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20tank's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdrones-in-armenia-azerbaijan-war-raises-doubt-about-tanks-future-2020-11%5C%22%3Epoor%20showing%20in%20recent%20conflicts%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20Eurasia%20stems%20more%20from%20decisions%20about%20how%20to%20employ%20those%20tanks%20rather%20than%20from%20failings%20of%20the%20tank%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUkraine%20mostly%20confirms%20that%20tanks%20remain%20survivable%2C%20and%20other%20conflicts%20confirm%20that%20some%20are%20more%20survivable%20than%20others%2C%26quot%3B%20Sam%20Cranny-Evans%20wrote%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feuro-sd.com%2F2023%2F01%2Farticles%2F29152%2Flessons-from-ukraine-armoured-fighting-vehicles%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEuropean%20Security%20and%20Defence%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20question%20raised%20by%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20whether%20the%20ratio%20of%20anti-tank%20guided%20missiles%2C%20known%20as%20ATGMs%2C%20to%20tanks%20has%20been%20so%20extreme%20as%20to%20distort%20any%20conclusions.%20%26quot%3BOne%20element%20of%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20that%20is%20perhaps%20unique%2C%20however%2C%20is%20the%20sheer%20mass%20of%20ATGMs%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20Cranny-Evans%2C%20who%20was%20previously%20a%20land-warfare%20researcher%20at%20the%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%2C%20a%20British%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226658%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20soldier%20fires%20a%20rocket%20gun%20as%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20in%20the%20Donetsk%20region%2C%20where%20the%20country's%20most%20intense%20clashes%20occur%2C%20attend%20intensive%20combat%20training%20by%20using%20both%20domestic%20and%20foreign%20weapons%20amid%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20in%20Donetsk%2C%20Ukraine%20on%20May%2008%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6464e75b0d92400018e6cd96%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224994%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20fires%20a%20rocket%20during%20weapons%20training%20in%20Donetsk%20in%20May.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20Muhammed%20Enes%20Yildirim%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20present%20in%20such%20numbers%20that%20units%20feel%20comfortable%20using%20them%20to%20engage%20bunkers%2C%20trucks%2C%20light%20armored%20vehicles%2C%20personnel%2C%20and%20any%20other%20target%20that%20can%20be%20justified%2C%26quot%3B%20Cranny-Evans%20wrote%20in%20reference%20to%20Ukrainian%20forces%2C%20noting%20that%20such%20%26quot%3Bfree-spirited%20use%26quot%3B%20of%20anti-tank%20missiles%20had%20been%20seen%20in%20previous%20wars%2C%20including%20by%20US%20forces%20in%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20experts%20have%20done%20for%2050%20years%2C%20Cranny-Evans%20pointed%20to%20the%201973%20Yom%20Kippur%20War%2C%20in%20which%20Arab%20armies%20used%20extremely%20dense%20concentrations%20of%20Soviet-made%20Sagger%20anti-tank%20missiles%20and%20RPG-7%20rockets%20to%20devastate%20Israeli%20tanks.%20Israeli%20armor%20made%20unsupported%20cavalry%20charges%20against%20Arab%20infantry%2C%20and%20tank%20units%20were%20committed%20piecemeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Yom%20Kippur%20war%20served%20to%20illustrate%20that%20massed%20ATGM%20deployments%20could%20blunt%20a%20massed%20armor%20advance%2C%20but%20also%20reinforced%20the%20lesson%20already%20known%20from%20World%20War%20II%20(arguably%20even%20WWI)%2C%20that%20armored%20vehicles%20alone%20were%20vulnerable%2C%26quot%3B%20Cranny-Evans%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20large-scale%20tank%20operations%20have%20been%20rare%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20perhaps%20because%20of%20steady%20attrition%20of%20armored%20forces%20or%20because%20the%20front%20lines%20are%20too%20large%20to%20allow%20either%20side%20the%20luxury%20of%20concentrating%20its%20armor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Destroyed%20Russian%20tank%20in%20Kherson%20Ukraine%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6527ff6c55f52b01b35dd465%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20destroyed%20Russian%20tank%20near%20a%20liberated%20Ukrainian%20village%20in%20Kherson%20province%20in%20November%202022.%3Cp%3ECelestino%20Arce%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNeither%20side%20appears%20capable%20%E2%80%94%20or%20willing%20%E2%80%94%20of%20forming%20much%20more%20than%20a%20company-sized%20battle%20group%20for%20offensive%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20Cranny-Evans%20wrote.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20many%20engagements%20involving%20armor%20have%20seen%20small%20numbers%20of%20tanks%20face%20large%20numbers%20of%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20apparent%20that%20advancing%20against%20an%20enemy%20with%20only%20one%20or%20two%20tanks%20and%20a%20small%20contingent%20of%20infantry%2C%20when%20ATGMs%20are%20present%20is%20unlikely%20to%20yield%20results%2C%26quot%3B%20Cranny-Evans%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThe%20defender%20may%20only%20have%20to%20destroy%20or%20disable%20a%20few%20vehicles%20in%20order%20to%20deter%20the%20attacker%20from%20proceeding%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20magnifies%20the%20effect%20of%20ATGMs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20the%201973%20war%2C%20the%20Israel%20Defense%20Forces%20had%20switched%20to%20combined-arms%20warfare%20and%20more%20sensible%20attacks%2C%20which%20enabled%20Israeli%20armored%20units%20to%20secure%20a%20partial%20victory.%20The%20IDF%20also%20incorporated%20lessons%20of%201973%2C%20such%20as%20safer%20ammunition%20stowage%20and%20less%20flammable%20hydraulic%20fluids%2C%20into%20the%20design%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-merkava-tank-replace-tanks-sent-to-ukraine-russia-war-2023-7%5C%22%3Eits%20well-protected%20Merkava%20tanks%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202006%20Lebanon%20War%2C%20while%20about%2050%20Israeli%20tanks%20were%20hit%20by%20missiles%2C%20only%2021%20had%20their%20armor%20penetrated%20and%20only%2010%20suffered%20crew%20casualties%2C%20Cranny-Evans%20noted%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Btherefore%20possible%20for%20modern%20tanks%20to%20withstand%20high%20levels%20of%20ATGM%20attacks%20without%20the%20crew%20or%20vehicle%20becoming%20incapacitated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukraine%20anti-tank%20missile%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65270e0c6561dd877e782cda%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221383%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20troops%20display%20anti-tank%20missiles%2C%20including%20NLAW%20and%20Javelin%2C%20at%20an%20exhibition%20in%20Lviv%20in%20December%202022.%3Cp%3EYURIY%20DYACHYSHYN%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ATGM%20threat%20also%20spurred%20the%20IDF%20to%20develop%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Farmys-tanks-will-soon-get-trophy-active-protection-system-2019-10%5C%22%3Eactive-protection%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20Trophy%2C%20which%20essentially%20use%20shotgun-like%20pellets%20to%20destroy%20or%20deflect%20anti-tank%20projectiles.%20Against%20opponents%20lacking%20deep%20anti-armor%20capabilities%2C%20this%20will%20do%20much%20to%20enhance%20tank%20survivability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20of%20a%20peer%20conflict%20such%20as%20Ukraine%2C%20where%20both%20sides%20are%20fielding%20heavily%20mechanized%20armies%20with%20plentiful%20anti-tank%20weapons%3F%20The%20fighting%20there%20may%20not%20r