andy%20(CG%2060)%20steam%20in%20formation%20in%20the%20Ionian%20Sea%2C%20Aug.%2020%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%20Photo%20by%20Mass%20Communication%20Specialist%203rd%20Class%20Maxwell%20Orlosky%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20was%20commissioned%20over%20five%20years%20ago%20and%20was%20in%20development%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%20The%20price%20tag%20of%20the%20first-in-class%20carrier%2C%20often%20over%20budget%20and%20behind%20schedule%20during%20its%20development%2C%20was%20a%20whopping%20%2413%20billion.%20It%20set%20out%20on%20a%20short%20maiden%20deployment%20last%20year%20and%20its%20first%20full%20deployment%20as%20part%20of%20a%20fully%20certified%20carrier%20strike%20group%20earlier%20this%20year.%20That%20deployment%20is%20ongoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20challenges%20in%20fielding%20the%20carrier%2C%20the%20Ford%20represents%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-admiral-navy-too-much-new-tech-aircraft-carrier-ford-2021-8%5C%22%3Econsiderable%20upgrade%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20previous%20Nimitz-class%20aircraft%20carriers.%20It%20boasts%20faster%20aircraft%20sorties%20and%20a%20smaller%20crew%2C%20with%20the%20Electromagnetic%20Aircraft%20Launch%20System%20(EMALS)%20and%20Advanced%20Arresting%20Gear%20(AAG)%20allowing%20fixed-wing%20aircraft%20to%20launch%20more%20smoothly%20and%20effectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Ford's%20electromagnetic%20catapult%20and%20arresting%20gear%20allow%20it%20to%20launch%20and%20recover%20aircraft%20faster%20than%20other%20carriers%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said.%20He%20added%20that%20those%20capabilities%20may%20have%20less%20of%20an%20impact%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20the%20flights%20are%20so%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20in%20areas%20like%20the%20eastern%20Mediterranean%2C%20%26quot%3Bbeing%20able%20to%20rapidly%20launch%20aircraft%20could%20enable%20the%20Ford%20to%20respond%20to%20air%20threats%20much%20faster%20than%20even%20ground-based%20aircraft.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ford%20is%20operating%20with%20eight%20squadrons%20of%20attack%20and%20support%20aircraft%2C%20per%20US%20Central%20Command.%20Carrier%20Airwing%208%20is%20tasked%20with%20defense%20of%20the%20carrier%20and%20conducting%20sustained%20air%20operations%20and%20consists%20of%20aviation%20assets%20such%20as%20multirole%20F%2FA-18E%2FF%20Super%20Hornets%2C%20electronic%20warfare%20EA-18G%20Growlers%2C%20early%20warning%20planes%20like%20the%20E-2D%20Hawkeye%2C%20and%20rotary%20aircraft.%20Carrier%20air%20wings%20typically%20have%20more%20than%2070%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20carrier's%20new%20technologies%2C%20the%20dual-band%20radar%2C%20capable%20of%20operating%20two%20frequency%20ranges%2C%20is%20also%20a%20major%20boon%20for%20operations%20and%20logistics%2C%20bolstering%20air%20defenses%20and%20surveillance.%20And%20the%20Ford's%20advanced%20weapons%20elevators%20were%20designed%20to%20transport%20larger%20and%20more%20complex%20munitions%20and%20systems%20much%20quicker%20to%20the%20flight%20deck%2C%20enabling%20the%20fast%20operations%20for%20which%20the%20carrier%20Ford%20was%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222133%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20E%2FA-18G%20Growler%20attached%20to%20the%20%26quot%3BGray%20Wolves%26quot%3B%20of%20Electronic%20Attack%20Squadron%20(VAQ)%20142%20takes%20off%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20(CVN%2078)%20during%20flight%20operations%20in%20the%20Adriatic%20Sea%2C%20Sept.%2013%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65281e8f55f52b01b35e11bb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221422%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20E%2FA-18G%20Growler%20attached%20to%20the%20%26quot%3BGray%20Wolves%26quot%3B%20of%20Electronic%20Attack%20Squadron%20(VAQ)%20142%20takes%20off%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20(CVN%2